00:44:02,173 --> 00:44:05,410
I've been staying awake
two nights in a row
memorizing genetic sequences.

714
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:07,212
Trying to impress me.

715
00:44:07,278 --> 00:44:09,147
Always, sir.

716
00:44:09,214 --> 00:44:11,817
How's your fiancee?
Good, great.

717
00:44:11,883 --> 00:44:15,620
I mean, uh, we've
both got school.
(CLEARS THROAT)

718
00:44:15,687 --> 00:44:18,256
And then there's the wedding.
So, it's a lot.

719
00:44:18,323 --> 00:44:20,759
I bet.
Well, I'd better get going.

720
00:44:20,826 --> 00:44:22,928
But have a good evening.

721
00:44:22,994 --> 00:44:25,630
You, too, Philip, and
try to get some rest.
Okay. Yeah, I will.

722
00:44:38,810 --> 00:44:40,178
Hey.
Hey. I'm sorry.

723
00:44:40,245 --> 00:44:41,379
You didn't give me a kiss
when you got in.

724
00:44:41,446 --> 00:44:42,814
I know, I didn't
want to wake you...

725
00:44:42,881 --> 00:44:44,182
Oh, my God.
What happened to your neck?

726
00:44:44,249 --> 00:44:46,351
A woman went psychotic
in the ER tonight.

727
00:44:46,417 --> 00:44:48,286
It was crazy. She went nuts.

728
00:44:48,353 --> 00:44:50,355
She hurt a nurse, so I had to
step in and do something.

729
00:44:50,989 --> 00:44:52,457
My hero.

730
00:44:54,359 --> 00:44:55,927
Wash up and come to bed.

731
00:45:05,370 --> 00:45:07,405
(WOMAN CRYING)

732
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:14,880
We may have just
caught a break.

733
00:45:14,946 --> 00:45:17,415
A friend of Julissa's
just called,
got me into her phone.

734
00:45:17,482 --> 00:45:20,318
We have the text
she got from the last guy
she had an appointment with.

735
00:45:20,385 --> 00:45:22,754
Now, if digital forensics
can get an IP off that,

736
00:45:22,821 --> 00:45:25,056
we can get an address,
maybe even a name.

737
00:45:25,123 --> 00:45:27,458
That'll take, what,
a couple of days?
At least.

738
00:45:27,525 --> 00:45:30,295
(WOMAN CRYING OUT)

739
00:45:30,361 --> 00:45:32,831
How'd he meet her?
Another ad on Craigslist?

740
00:45:32,898 --> 00:45:34,165
Looks like that.

741
00:45:36,134 --> 00:45:39,204
I don't get it.
This day and age, girl's
in a friggin' hotel room,

742
00:45:39,270 --> 00:45:41,706
a guy she doesn't
even know... I just...

743
00:45:44,709 --> 00:45:47,245
Mrs. Flores,
Detective Bennett.

744
00:45:47,312 --> 00:45:49,214
Sorry for the loss
of your daughter.

745
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:50,816
She was a good girl.

746
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:53,584
I'm sure she was.

747
00:45:53,651 --> 00:45:55,787
She was just getting
her life together.

748
00:45:57,956 --> 00:45:59,524
Who would do this?

749
00:46:00,792 --> 00:46:02,861
Who would do this
to my baby?

750
00:46:20,778 --> 00:46:23,048
Used to be able
to see who the
bad guys were, right?

751
00:46:23,114 --> 00:46:26,217
Now it's all texts and
emails and websites.

752
00:46:26,284 --> 00:46:29,487
The creeps are hiding
in our houses, and

753
00:46:29,554 --> 00:46:31,389
we don't even
know who they are.

754
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:35,626
It is 7:07 and
once again, here's Matt.

755
00:46:35,693 --> 00:46:37,662
All right, Meredith,
thank you. And now to
a story out of Boston

756
00:46:37,728 --> 00:46:40,798
that's gonna terrify anyone
who's ever placed a classified
ad, especially online.

757
00:46:40,866 --> 00:46:42,400
Wow, this is in Boston.

758
00:46:42,467 --> 00:46:44,035
What's that?
MATT: A man is apparently
targeting women

759
00:46:44,102 --> 00:46:45,303
who place ads on
the popular website...

760
00:46:45,370 --> 00:46:46,838
This guy's right
here in Boston.

761
00:46:46,905 --> 00:46:49,540
...Craigslist. Police say
he's already killed one woman

762
00:46:49,607 --> 00:46:51,042
(PHONE RINGING)
and attacked
another in Boston.

763
00:46:53,511 --> 00:46:55,981
Hello?
SUSAN: Hey, Megan, it's Mom.

764
00:46:56,047 --> 00:46:57,682
Listen, I was
watching the news,

765
00:46:57,748 --> 00:47:02,620
and I saw this story about
this Boston hotel killer.

766
00:47:02,687 --> 00:47:06,357
No, we're not staying
in a hotel. We're here,
home, studying.

767
00:47:06,424 --> 00:47:07,658
Me and Philip are safe.

768
00:47:08,259 --> 00:47:09,560
Okay.

769
00:47:09,627 --> 00:47:11,129
I love you.
I love you, too.

770
00:47:11,196 --> 00:47:12,397
Bye.

771
00:47:16,734 --> 00:47:19,037
PROFILER: Of course,
the profile is never exact,

772
00:47:19,104 --> 00:47:24,209
but a pretty clear picture
is emerging of what
we're looking for.

773
00:47:24,275 --> 00:47:26,411
We're talking about a guy

774
00:47:26,477 --> 00:47:29,547
with an inability to
form close emotional
relationships with women.

775
00:47:29,614 --> 00:47:31,316
Probably sexual issues.

776
00:47:34,252 --> 00:47:38,056
A loner. A guy who shies
away from the crowd.

777
00:47:40,725 --> 00:47:42,493
Maybe later. Come on.

778
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:43,728
What's up?
Let's go.

779
00:47:43,794 --> 00:47:45,296
You didn't even
give me a chance.

780
00:47:45,363 --> 00:47:49,034
PROFILER: A man with no sense
of status, accomplishment.

781
00:47:50,568 --> 00:47:52,971
Let me get this straight.

782
00:47:53,038 --> 00:47:57,675
We're looking for
a big, blond loser wearing
a Red Sox cap in Boston?

783
00:47:57,742 --> 00:47:59,577
Is that what
you're telling me?

784
00:47:59,644 --> 00:48:02,380
Let's get right on
that one. We should have
that settled by morning.

785
00:48:02,447 --> 00:48:04,482
Thanks for the crack
work, Detective.

786
00:48:05,984 --> 00:48:07,685
Maybe somebody
will ID the photo.

787
00:48:07,752 --> 00:48:10,121
We got a blurry photo
with the same damn guy

788
00:48:10,188 --> 00:48:12,790
wearing the same friggin' hat.
This is just going great.

789
00:48:12,857 --> 00:48:16,061
REPORTER: Police are now
hoping someone out there
recognizes this man

790
00:48:16,127 --> 00:48:19,230
from all the surveillance
photos in the various hotels.

791
00:48:19,297 --> 00:48:21,732
They are trying to get onto
his track this morning,

792
00:48:21,799 --> 00:48:23,401
but so far,
they have no leads.

793
00:48:23,468 --> 00:48:25,803
But police say
the warning is out
to women now

794
00:48:25,870 --> 00:48:27,738
that this man is
still on the loose,

795
00:48:27,805 --> 00:48:31,109
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
especially if you post
ads on Craigslist. Matt.

796
00:48:32,944 --> 00:48:35,981
Who is it?
MARCELO: Marcelo,
superintendent.

797
00:48:40,485 --> 00:48:41,852
I need to
talk to you.

798
00:48:47,192 --> 00:48:49,727
Oh, my God.
That's amazing.

799
00:48:49,794 --> 00:48:51,496
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
WOMAN: Nice.

800
00:48:54,032 --> 00:48:57,702
All right, that's it for me.
I'm cashing out. I'm done.

801
00:48:57,768 --> 00:48:59,204
I'm sorry, I gotta go.

802
00:49:00,471 --> 00:49:02,907
I've got another date,
ladies. I'm so sorry.

803
00:49:03,741 --> 00:49:05,210
CASHIER: $5,300.

804
00:49:20,125 --> 00:49:21,959
VOICEMAIL: You have
three new messages.

805
00:49:22,027 --> 00:49:25,930
MEGAN: Hey, Philip. I need to
talk to you. Where are you?

806
00:49:25,997 --> 00:49:27,932
MEGAN: Philip, call me.
I need to talk to you, okay?

807
00:49:28,966 --> 00:49:30,835
VOICEMAIL: Message deleted.

808
00:49:30,901 --> 00:49:33,238
MEGAN: Baby, where are you?
Call me as soon as...
No, no.

809
00:49:33,304 --> 00:49:34,805
VOICEMAIL: Message deleted.

810
00:49:36,241 --> 00:49:38,043
Hey, your client
there yet?

811
00:49:38,109 --> 00:49:40,178
He called and said
he'd be, like, 10 minutes.

812
00:49:40,245 --> 00:49:42,680
All right, well, text me
when he gets there.

813
00:49:42,747 --> 00:49:44,882
Promise. Love you, sweetheart.

814
00:49:44,949 --> 00:49:46,117
I love you, too, babe.

815
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:55,860
You're a young one.
Come on in.

816
00:50:00,631 --> 00:50:02,867
It's just a lap dance
like the ad said, okay?

817
00:50:03,701 --> 00:50:05,303
That's all I came for, yeah.

818
00:50:11,409 --> 00:50:14,179
Lie face-down on the floor.

819
00:50:14,245 --> 00:50:18,216
Lie face-down on the
floor right now! Put your
hands behind your back.

820
00:50:18,283 --> 00:50:20,818
Listen to me. I do not
want to kill you, okay?

821
00:50:20,885 --> 00:50:22,953
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

822
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:25,123
Who's calling your phone?
I don't know.

823
00:50:25,190 --> 00:50:27,325
Honey, take a seat.
Don't move, don't move.

824
00:50:27,392 --> 00:50:29,594
Get off! Get off!

825
00:50:29,660 --> 00:50:30,661
(SCREAMING)

826
00:50:32,230 --> 00:50:33,864
What the hell's
going on here, huh?

827
00:51:19,177 --> 00:51:21,179
INFOMERCIAL: ...just
call the toll-free
number on your screen

828
00:51:21,246 --> 00:51:23,348
for a free personal
enrollment kit.

829
00:51:23,414 --> 00:51:26,184
You're under no obligation
to enroll, and no
salesman will call.

830
00:51:26,251 --> 00:51:28,986
It's so easy to afford
peace of mind.

831
00:51:29,053 --> 00:51:31,088
The hunt for the man being
called "The Craigslist Killer"

832
00:51:31,156 --> 00:51:33,758
has spread this morning
from Boston to Rhode Island.

833
00:51:33,824 --> 00:51:37,195
Police in Warwick near
Providence are investigating
a robbery attempt

834
00:51:37,262 --> 00:51:41,166
that may involve the
same man who killed two
young women in Boston.

835
00:51:41,232 --> 00:51:43,901
Boston police
say the murderer
apparently targeted...

836
00:52:01,085 --> 00:52:03,020
I thought you
said, "No secrets."

837
00:52:04,922 --> 00:52:06,090
What are you talking about?

838
00:52:06,891 --> 00:52:08,092
Where have you been?

839
00:52:09,560 --> 00:52:11,929
What do you mean?
The super came by.

840
00:52:13,864 --> 00:52:15,633
You haven't paid the
rent in three months.

841
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:21,372
If there's something going on,
then I need to know before...

842
00:52:21,439 --> 00:52:23,241
Before what?
Before you marry me?

843
00:52:24,742 --> 00:52:27,212
I missed some bills, Meg.

844
00:52:27,278 --> 00:52:30,181
I'm sorry, okay?
I'm studying 20 hours a day.

845
00:52:30,248 --> 00:52:33,117
I've got millions of tons
of crap that I'm dealing with

846
00:52:33,184 --> 00:52:35,486
and professors on top of that.
But you know what?

847
00:52:35,553 --> 00:52:37,455
You're right, you're right.
I screwed up.

848
00:52:37,522 --> 00:52:39,290
I screwed up, and I'm...
You know what?

849
00:52:39,357 --> 00:52:42,159
I'm sorry that I'm not the
perfect guy you thought I was.

850
00:52:42,227 --> 00:52:43,494
I never asked you to
be the perfect guy.

851
00:52:43,561 --> 00:52:45,129
Then what are
you asking me?

852
00:52:45,196 --> 00:52:47,031
What do you want from me, Meg?

853
00:53:02,247 --> 00:53:04,148
I should've told
you first, okay?

854
00:53:04,215 --> 00:53:06,050
And I didn't. I just...

855
00:53:06,116 --> 00:53:07,952
I get in my own head
about things, and...

856
00:53:12,790 --> 00:53:15,926
It's been a really hard
time for me, you know?

857
00:53:15,993 --> 00:53:17,828
It's been a hard
time for me, too.

858
00:53:18,963 --> 00:53:22,333
I know, I know.

859
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:27,238
Look, I am...
I'm sorry, babe.
I am so sorry, okay?

860
00:53:27,305 --> 00:53:29,474
I haven't been there for you,
and I'm gonna be, all right?

861
00:53:29,540 --> 00:53:33,444
Baby, look at me.
It's my fault, okay?
But I am trying my best.

862
00:53:36,414 --> 00:53:38,483
I'll go down to the
management office tomorrow.

863
00:53:38,549 --> 00:53:40,518
I'll take care of it
right away, first thing.

864
00:53:41,986 --> 00:53:43,888
I promise, okay?

865
00:53:48,893 --> 00:53:50,661
God, I love you.

866
00:53:53,063 --> 00:53:55,866
I don't want to mess
this up, babe. I don't
want to lose you.

867
00:53:55,933 --> 00:53:57,234
I'm not going anywhere.

868
00:53:57,302 --> 00:53:58,836
You promise?
Yes.

869
00:53:58,903 --> 00:54:00,305
Good.

870
00:54:00,371 --> 00:54:02,206
Just, you need to
let me in, okay?

871
00:54:04,208 --> 00:54:06,411
I have no idea what
I did to deserve you.

872
00:54:24,395 --> 00:54:25,763
Lady got lucky.

873
00:54:25,830 --> 00:54:28,533
Husband was in the lobby,
came to check on her.

874
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:30,368
Hey, blow that up
for me, would you?

875
00:54:32,136 --> 00:54:35,773
Lieutenant? We tracked
an IP address for that
last email to Julissa.

876
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:37,708
Whoever sent it
lives in Quincy.

877
00:54:37,775 --> 00:54:40,378
He who kills by the Internet
fries by the Internet, right?

878
00:54:40,445 --> 00:54:42,547
He's not frying yet.
It's an apartment complex,

879
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:45,149
so the killer could've
been using somebody
else's wireless signal.

880
00:54:45,215 --> 00:54:47,418
All right, then I want a full
tenant list for that building.

881
00:54:47,485 --> 00:54:49,787
I want six units down there,
six invisible units.

882
00:54:49,854 --> 00:54:53,257
And I want 100 copies of this
picture blown up, all right?

883
00:54:53,324 --> 00:54:56,994
Let's hope the coffee's
good down in Quincy.

884
00:54:57,061 --> 00:54:59,129
BENNETT: No, no, no, no, no.
Listen to me, listen to me.

885
00:54:59,196 --> 00:55:01,432
I don't want you hanging
out in the mall on a
school night, all right?

886
00:55:01,499 --> 00:55:03,368
You understand?

887
00:55:03,434 --> 00:55:06,036
Okay, all right.
You got a ride?

888
00:55:08,906 --> 00:55:10,541
Do I know him?

889
00:55:12,477 --> 00:55:15,079
Okay. All right.

890
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:17,348
Great, I love you,
baby. I'll see you
back at the house.

891
00:55:19,049 --> 00:55:20,351
This guy is
driving me crazy.

892
00:55:20,418 --> 00:55:22,953
I mean, he's turning me
into my old man here.

893
00:55:23,020 --> 00:55:25,790
I'm two seconds
away from locking my
daughter up for good.

894
00:55:25,856 --> 00:55:27,558
Gotta let her go
at some point.

895
00:55:28,325 --> 00:55:29,860
Do I?

896
00:55:34,064 --> 00:55:36,601
FRYE: There's got to be
800 units in this place.

897
00:55:36,667 --> 00:55:39,203
Great. All we've got to do now
is wait for a guy to waltz by

898
00:55:39,269 --> 00:55:43,574
who looks like a
vicious, loner killer
with emotional issues.

899
00:55:50,648 --> 00:55:52,417
You're kidding me, right?

900
00:55:52,483 --> 00:55:54,218
This guy could be anybody.

901
00:55:54,284 --> 00:55:56,454
You got another picture
I can look at? Anything?

902
00:55:56,521 --> 00:55:58,656
Well, if you see anyone,
just give me a call.

903
00:56:08,132 --> 00:56:10,735
Hey. Before
we go...
What? What?

904
00:56:10,801 --> 00:56:14,071
What are we having
for dinner tonight?
Making something good?

905
00:56:14,138 --> 00:56:15,606
I don't know yet.

906
00:56:15,673 --> 00:56:18,175
You don't have
to cook tonight.
No, I want to.

907
00:56:18,242 --> 00:56:20,244
PHILIP: Okay.
Laundry time first, though.

908
00:56:26,784 --> 00:56:28,385
FRYE: IP came up with a name.

909
00:56:33,991 --> 00:56:35,259
Son of a bitch!

910
00:56:36,561 --> 00:56:39,029
"Philip Markoff, residing
in Quincy, Mass."

911
00:56:39,096 --> 00:56:41,432
BENNETT: Are you kidding me?

912
00:56:41,499 --> 00:56:45,436
I mean, come on, you put
a baseball cap on that freak,
we've definitely got our guy.

913
00:56:45,503 --> 00:56:47,171
He's a med student at B.U.

914
00:56:47,237 --> 00:56:49,474
Four hundred and
seventy-eight friends.

915
00:56:49,540 --> 00:56:52,477
Who the hell would
want 478 friends?

916
00:56:52,543 --> 00:56:55,613
"Religious views:
It's complicated."

917
00:56:55,680 --> 00:56:57,882
"Relationship status:
Engaged."

918
00:56:57,948 --> 00:56:59,383
Quite a catch,
this fella, huh!

919
00:56:59,450 --> 00:57:01,151
We can always bring
him in, question him.

920
00:57:01,218 --> 00:57:03,621
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no. We, uh...

921
00:57:03,688 --> 00:57:05,155
We stop by, he's not there.

922
00:57:05,222 --> 00:57:07,825
He hears we showed up,
he's off to Brazil.

923
00:57:07,892 --> 00:57:09,226
I don't want to spook him.

924
00:57:09,293 --> 00:57:12,096
You know, we just sit tight,
keep him under surveillance,

925
00:57:12,162 --> 00:57:15,099
get a positive ID
from the masseuse

926
00:57:15,165 --> 00:57:17,067
and nail him.

927
00:57:17,134 --> 00:57:19,436
REPORTER: And the hunt
for the so-called "Craigslist
Killer" is intensifying,

928
00:57:19,504 --> 00:57:22,473
with police hoping to catch
him before he strikes again.

929
00:57:38,523 --> 00:57:40,625
Jeff Rossen has the
latest now from Boston.

930
00:57:41,859 --> 00:57:44,361
See? This is way better.

931
00:57:44,428 --> 00:57:46,797
JEFF: The police are literally
going hotel to hotel now

932
00:57:46,864 --> 00:57:48,032
here in the Boston area...

933
00:57:48,098 --> 00:57:49,433
Wow, this is everywhere.

934
00:57:49,500 --> 00:57:51,001
...showing these
surveillance photos around.

935
00:57:51,068 --> 00:57:52,570
MEGAN: That could be anybody.

936
00:57:52,637 --> 00:57:54,038
They're worried he's
planning his next attack.

937
00:57:54,104 --> 00:57:55,540
I'm gonna be right back.
Yeah, are you all right?

938
00:57:55,606 --> 00:57:57,141
Yeah.

939
00:57:57,207 --> 00:58:00,077
JEFF: Over the weekend,
investigators pored
through nearly two...

940
00:58:00,144 --> 00:58:02,880
If you're still mad,
I'd just rather we called
the whole thing off.

941
00:58:02,947 --> 00:58:04,982
(EXHALES)

942
00:58:05,049 --> 00:58:06,884
ACTRESS: You
certainly have an...

943
00:58:50,995 --> 00:58:52,930
ACTRESS: Until I met you...
Hey, you know what?

944
00:58:52,997 --> 00:58:54,599
ACTRESS: ...I didn't know it
